CatDescriptText: Mr. Gustave McClung, 10 Cornet Street, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 28, 1958, pg. 3 with question: "What do you think is wrong with the Pittsburgh Pirates? Do you think that they are using their best ball players at all times?" answer reads: "Yes, I think that a policeman has the free hand to make arrests."
